It's light-bodied and slightly sweet with a refreshingly crisp finish. Pair with Thai cuisine, grilled pork chops or enjoy in a tall glass with ice before a meal.

hasMenuItem.name: Strongbow 440mL 5.3% ABV

BRAVE IS AS BRAVE DOES!

hasMenuItem.name: Peller Estate Pinot Grigio Bottle 750mL 12% ABV

hasMenuItem.name: Copper Moon Pinot Grigio Bottle 750mL 12% ABV
hasMenuItem.description: Pale lemon yellow colour with a beautiful aroma of citrus, green apple and ripe pear. Copper Moon Pinot Grigio is a light-bodied wine with refreshing flavours of citrus and melon. Slight floral notes linger on through the finish.

hasMenuItem.name: Peller Estate Chard Bottle 750mL 12.5% ABV
hasMenuItem.description: A medium-bodied, smooth yet refreshing Chardonnay. Flavours of ripe juicy orchard fruits unfold on the palate. Just a splash of fresh acidity cleanses the palate, while juicy ripe apples and pears, along with a touch of citrus, spice, and sweet oak linger on the finish.

hasMenuItem.name: Peller Estate Merlot Bottle 750mL 14.2% ABV
hasMenuItem.description: Deep garnet colour with a bouquet of black cherry, dark blue plum, sweet vanilla extract and dark chocolate. This medium to full-bodied Merlot has soft yet drying tannins and flavours of red and black berries, dark plum, cherry and spice.

hasMenuItem.name: Peller Estate Cab Merlot Bottle 750mL 13.7% ABV
hasMenuItem.description: Ruby purple; aromas and flavours of black fruit and cocoa, with notes of fresh herb; dry, medium bodied, with crisp but balanced acidity.

hasMenuItem.name: Red Rooster Pinot Noir 750mL 12.5% ABV
hasMenuItem.description: This is a great red wine to go with many food items such as salmon steaks, roasted poultry or pasta. Taste the red berry and cherry fruit with your menu or occasion.

hasMenuItem.name: Copper Moon Sauvignon Blanc Bottle 750mL 12% ABV
hasMenuItem.description: The Sauvignon Blanc grapes used for this wine are pressed, cool fermented and aged in stainless steel to retain fruit characteristics.A light-bodied wine with refreshing flavours of apple, peach and citrus.

hasMenuItem.name: J Lohr Cab Bottle 375 mL 13.9% ABV
hasMenuItem.description: Classic barrel-aged Cabernet with high-toned fruit and a lovely bouquet of hazelnut and toasted pastry. This dark color Cabernet has a bright hue at release. Boasting layered fruit aromas of cherry and plum, accented by an authentic barrel bouquet of hazelnut, dark chocolate and toasted pastry.

review.reviewBody: delicious,  gravy is a bit on the salty side but I enjoyed it over all.

This is the worst mac and cheese I have ever had!  What I received was a container partially filled with dry cooked noodles or noodles covered in an oily garlic substance. There is a tiny sprinkling and I am talking maybe a half teaspoon of shredded cheese, on  top but no cheese sauce at all.

  Mac and cheese is pretty simple to make, you make a white béchamel sauce with milk or cream, butter and  a small amount flour to thicken, add several cups of shredded cheese, stir until cheese is melted and well mixed, then pour it over cooked pasta. It is not difficult at all!

 The "garlic bread" is a bread "finger", not a slice of bread. It measures by 1/2 and inch by 4 inches long and that is laughable!! Literally a finger sized piece of toast, not even close to being a slice of bread, let alone traditional a traditional garlic bread loaf piece! 

 I took a photo and was literally not  "allowed" to attach it to this review.....that is telling! Needless to say, I will not be ordering from here again!
The Mac Attack is not as advertised. No garlic bread or breadcrumbs, no herbs. It's literally pasta you can make at home. Very disappointing.

The soup was fantastic!

The pasta had to be tossed - the chicken tasted like bad fish and made it inedible.
The cheese flavour is very mild for me personally.
